original: Cederbom, Erik Johan Theodor (Thore), kyrkoherde, N. Fågelås, Hjo, f. 27/1/01 i Vilske-Kleva, Skarab. 1., av Johannes C. o. Lydia Johansson. — G. 31 m. Ingeborg Claeson. Barn: Gunnar f. 32, Gerd 34, Hans 40. — Studiex. i Skara 23, teol. ex. o. prästv. s. å. Past:adj. i N. Ving 30, kommin. i Lekåsa 31, kyrkoh. i N. o. S. Fågel-ås sed. 41. Ordf. i kyrkoråd, kyrkostämma o. folksk :styr.
translated: Cederbom, Erik Johan Theodor (Thore), clergyman, N. Fågelås, Hjo, born January 27, 1901 in Vilske-Kleva, Skaraborg County, son of Johannes C. and Lydia Johansson. Married in 1931 to Ingeborg Claeson. Children: Gunnar born in 1932, Gerd in 1934, and Hans in 1940. Completed his studies in Skara in 1923, ordained as a priest the same year. Served as a curate in N. Ving in 1930, a chaplain in Lekåsa in 1931, and as a vicar in N. and S. Fågelås from 1941. Also served as chairman of the church council, church meeting, and the board of education.
